PROCESS      HELP=*
PARM INP       TYPE=STRING   COUNT=2:10
PARM OUT       TYPE=STRING   COUNT=(1:3)
PARM BORDER    TYPE=INTEGER  COUNT=1 DEFAULT=2
PARM CHIPROW   TYPE=INTEGER  COUNT=1 DEFAULT=5
PARM COLS      TYPE=INTEGER  COUNT=2 DEFAULT=(1,2)
PARM CHIPSIZE  TYPE=INTEGER  COUNT=1 DEFAULT=256
PARM INPSTACK  TYPE=INTEGER  COUNT=(0:9) DEFAULT=0
PARM TEXTCOL   TYPE=INTEGER  COUNT=1 DEFAULT=0
END-PROC

.TITLE
VICAR/IBIS Program "chipper2"

.HELP
PURPOSE
 This program converts the east/north coordinates from
 the ibis file into x/y coordinates of the input image
 and creates and output image consisting of 256x256
 chips of those coordinates.  The input should be:

 inp=(ibis file, input image1, input img2, input img3)

 where images 2 and 3 are optional.  If more than 1
 input image is specified the input images are assumed
 to be coregistered.  The input images must also have
 the same size and format.

 The INPSTACK is and optional parameter that specifies
 how the input files are grouped.  For example:

 inp=(ibisfile, input in1, input in2, input in3,
      input in4)
 inpstack=(1,2,1)
 out=(output out1, output out2)

 will create 2 images where the columns of the images
 will be:

 out1 = (img1, img2, img4)
 out2 = (img1, img3, img4)

 The number of output images must match the largest
 inpstack number.  The sum of the inpstack number
 must also match the sum of input files.

 The CHIPROW parameter specifies how many chips to
 display per row.  If more than 1 image is input or
 more than 1 inpstack is specified, then CHIPROW 
 parameter is ignored and the number of chips
 per row is set to number of input images (such that
 chips from different input images can be viewed side
 by side).  If more than 1 inpstack is specified,
 then the number of chips per row is set to number
 of input stacks.

 The TEXTCOL parameter specifies a column in the
 ibis file that contains text to write onto the chips.
 It is an optional parameter and the ibis column
 must be a string column.

.LEVEL1
.VARIABLE INP
 Input ibis and image file(s)

.VARIABLE OUT
 Output image file

.VARIABLE BORDER
 Size of the border between
 chips

.VARIABLE CHIPROW
 Number of chips to display
 per row in the output file

.VARIABLE COLS
 Columns in the ibis file that
 specifies the east/north
 coordinates repectively

.VARIABLE INPSTACK
 Specifies how the inputs
 should be stacked together
 to create more than 1
 output image

.VARIABLE TEXTCOL
 Column in the ibis file
 that contains text to
 write onto the chips.
 The ibis column must be
 a string column.

.END











